values:
Tuesday before I left, I went to one of our producers' houses to help her with her taxes and email. I was struggling with whether to go or not, she said she'd pay me $100 cash for the afternoon and I wanted to go but I was so worried that if I did, she'd start to see me as an 'assistant'/office worker type and not as an artist. I probably over-think these things, but I get so cautious about that - I just see how Lindsey got pulled into doing a lot of administrative, non-creative work and I can't have that for myself. I was talking to Jason about it, I said I wanted to go, I don't mind doing data work and I needed the money. "I'll pay you $150 <i>not</I> to go," he said. I am so in love with him, you guys. He is so supportive and he really, truly knows what I'm worth and what I'm capable of. Ultimately, I did go and I'm really glad I did because her house was fucking BEAUTIFUL and it was in the top of the hills - it was fucking terrifying getting there and back - but it was such a lovely, relaxing day. Even doing work. It was the first genuine <i>quiet</i> I think I've had in two months. She showed me what to do and then left so I had amazing Liss time all day in her beautiful home, with her TOTALLY SWEET CAT called Hello Kitty. &hearts; &hearts; &hearts; 

<lj-cut text="In other news, I'm homesies!~ &hearts; &hearts; &hearts;">In other news, I'm homesies!~ &hearts; &hearts; &hearts;

My travel day was a bit hellish, my cab was SO late coming to get me (probably #1 thing I hate about LA, no one is ever on time) and I was freaking out but I got there in time. There was a woman ahead of me in the security line who was crying because she lost her phone. I couldn't feel bad for her because she mentioned literally three times that she missed her flight because she ~stopped for a cocktail~. Or five, probably. Also, an observation - alcoholics use the word "cocktail" an awful lot, I think it's an effort to distance themselves from the alcohol, it doesn't sound as incriminating as "a drink". IDEK. Anyway. So she had this total breakdown in the middle of the airport, another woman next to me had the patience of a goddamn saint trying to help her. She started bawling and the nice lady was like, "What's wrong now?" and the drunk lady was like, "I'VE HAD A SHIT LIFE, OKAY!" Who the fuck hasn't, amirite. Also, who hasn't ever lost their phone lol.

I had a layover in Vegas. I asked Jason's friend Paul (the one who took me to Cirque) if he wanted to do happy hour but he was busy. P.S. I designed his business cards and they came out so totally sexy, you guys!~ I need to make mahself some new business cards. ANYWAY, I DIGRESS. I just got a bagel and a banana, before I found some desk space with powar and finished this fucking ~schedule~ that I know ultimately won't matter anyway. It was apparently urgent but I sent it on Wednesday, and have yet to hear back from anybody. That's the stuff I'm getting sick of - don't tell me you need stuff ASAP and stress me out about it if you're going to ignore it for (at least) a week. Oh, and! My second flight was on a different airline? So I had to get my luggage, cart it all the way around the airport, and go through security again. A mistake I will never make again, also my suitcase sucks BALLS, ugh UGH IT ALWAYS TIPS. And! I had to pay for it to go through twice! So fucking ridiculous!

I tried to sleep on the plane but couldn't - on the way to Vegas I had a whole row to myself and still couldn't sleep, the flight was so short. On the way home, I watched shows until my computer died. There was a screaming child, and also the bitch next to me was disgusting - she had taken her shoes off, which is fine, whatever, except she was like, curling into a ball on her seat, ~laying on her boyfriend~ and putting her foot in the crack next to my seat. Fucking GROSS. And she never stopped moving. Every five minutes she'd make a huge production out of trying to contort into some new "sleeping" position, BITCH YOU ARE ON AN AIRPLANE, NOT AT THE RADISSON. Sleep in your gd seat, with a neck pillow if you must.

I was so excited to see Jason, I came out the doors with a huge smile but when I was about four feet away from him I burst into tears. We hugged for ages and I wish I could have seen it from the outside. I love airports. Sometimes I'm surprised that more people don't act like he and I did, don't express as much - just give a "HI!" and a kiss on the cheek - but the idea of it all. I can't say I've ever witnessed such an out-pour as an outsider but I know I will someday, I know it does happen every day. I couldn't stop touching him in the car, it was so strange, it was like we had just started dating even though it's been a year. And being in LA, I've been constantly aware of my surroundings, you know? Constantly looking for and at new things. That has carried over - I saw several things on the car ride home that I've never noticed before, even though I've lived here my whole life. I've also been a little unsure about these roads - I still know where I'm going, I just doubt my turns for a split second. It's really weird. </lj-cut>

I got in at midnight so we just came to Jason's. I got off the elevator and saw his window across the way - he'd turned his Christmas lights on. &hearts; When I walked in, I saw this:

<center><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v676/lissiexanga/319863_10101846010287520_13958666_76642052_1387887549_n.jpg" width="450"></center>
I can't. And you can't see it in the picture but the cutest, unintentional cute thing about it is that he brought in a little spolight because he needed it to be lit properly. &hearts; I love dating an artistic, Apple fanboy. He got a bonus at work, so he got himself the new iPad and me a new Mac. &hearts; AND, god, those tiny things - fruit snacks, chocolate, and chapstick. And that's a bottle of my favorite riesling. It is like, me on a table. And A NEW COMPUTER - you guys, Mia was totally dying and I just kljshfjklas. And he got it with a fancy no-glare screen so I can photoshop/write outside. He told me it wasn't just a computer, it was an investment in my future because he knows I'm going to be great. And he put Adobe CS5 on it and Final Cut and Final Draft and Aperture and I can't, I can't. I feel like I sound like such a spoiled brat or that I'm not making a big deal out of this but I am really, truly appreciative and almost can't even believe that I've found someone so sweet. He tells me I deserve it, that it means a lot to him that he's able to do this after I took a chance on and stuck by him when he was in debt, in a crappy apartment with a mattress on the floor. I'm really proud of him. If I look at the Jason I knew before we started dating and the way he is now, it is a night and day difference. 

He made me stir fry at 2 in the morning. And shit like that - unique, out of the ordinary circumstances however small just... &hearts; We went to bed. "I'm home :)," I said up at him. "Now I'm home too," he replied. &hearts;
